<A>__{ into the echoing chaos of the corridor trying to move in the crowd shoving through to where people are yelling and clustered around a figure lying on the floor. willy pushes closer, until he catches glimpses of: nunally. lying on the marble floor. his gun in his lifeless fingers. blood all over, from his head. willy stops pushing. won't let himself look away the screams and commotion around him retreating into a numb blur. then suddenly willy looks up as if he's been called to find crawford, standing very still, in the crowd, on the other side of the body. everyone else is moving, talking, gawking at the body or averting their eyes except crawford. he's looking straight at willy. pleased. triumphant. willy stares into crawford's eyes.}
